Congratulations Bill from another Wilson. Later, Jay Wilson

Well Bill went to CPR yesterday afternoon.Had to pick something up and had a nice visit with Ray and Cathy to.Peacefull drive in and got 4 grouse on way in to get limit as I got one in morning going to my deer baits.Probably saw 2 dozen going in and out.
John you taking care of that new truck?make sure you don't get it bloody!!
great fish!! are you sure you were not up in the yukon? early october should be shorts, t shirt, barefoot..
My truck is a disaster area already.Good thing I got the vynil flooring in it.Can was it out.Yes there's blood on it and in it.There will be more.
Yel - A week ago Wed, it was 27 degrees in the morning. Remember, us folks from "The South" are just not used to such cool weather! Running down the lake helps to maintain that cool! Wink! Bill
John - Ya, we see some every trip in/out of CPR. Beautiful/best time of the year! Bill
Here's a best pic of my personal best, 31" from Cedar Lake, last week. Fish was successfully released. Sort of a Wilson over the fence shot, but no body cares what I look like, anyway! Bill
Congrats.. 30"+ walleye in Canada are rare and that is a great fish. Even better it is swimming for someone else !!!!

Very nice Bill, and glad it's back in to give me an opportunity to catch it next year!!
Ha! Scott - See you at the Cedar Falls show, in March(?). Bill
